<div> </div>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>Day 1:</strong> Land in Bergen and transfer to the city centre by shuttle bus. Spend the rest of the day exploring this vibrant city.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2:</strong> Today will start with meeting your local guide and having a walking tour of Bergen. Visiting all the main attractions, including the UNESCO World Heritage listed Bryggen, Church of Mary and the famous fish market on the waterfront. Once you have seen all of those great sites, take the Fløibanen Funicular to the top of Mount Fløyen for fantastic views over the whole city and see the gateway to the Fjords. </p>
<p><strong>Day 3:</strong> This morning you will take a scenic express boat down the Sognefjord, the longest and deepest Norwegian Fjord. Seeing small Norweigan towns and changes in the colourful fjord scenery along your way. After this scenic journey you will arrive in <a data-udi="umb://document/a09d8dda0d4f48d68be229cdaeb2f377" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a09d8dda0d4f48d68be229cdaeb2f377}" title="Balestrand">Balestrand</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4:</strong> Today is a day of leisure to discover the enchanting village of Balestrand at your own pace. Alternatively you can take the optional full day excursion to the idyllic village of Fjærland, which is known as 'where glacier meets the fjord', and its surrounding areas. Visiting two glaciers, Supphellebreen and Bøyabreen, and sailing through the beautiful Fjærland Fjord with its steep mountain and vibrant landscape.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5:</strong> Continuing along the Sognefjord, the Kind of Norway, your cruise will arrive in the charming village of Flåm. Taking the infamous Flåm Railway is definitely a highlight of this tour. You will pass the beautiful mountainous scenery with waterfalls to each side and travelling through 20 tunnels, on one of the steepest train-lines in the world! From the Flåm Railway you will swap to the great Bergen Railway to get you to the capital city of Oslo.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6:</strong> After breakfast you will meet your guide for some city sightseeing. Receive great insight to the vibrant capital city and its highlights, from the Frogner Park to the Royal Palace and Akershus Fortress. Then its time to visit Xperium, a 15 minute standing attraction on a journey to discover the Northern Lights. Take the rest of the day to wonder round the city and keep exploring! </p>
<p><strong>Day 7:</strong> Transfer to Oslo airport for your flight home.</p>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>What’s included</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from the UK to Bergen and back from Oslo</li>
<li>Return airport transfers (by Airport Shuttle, with the chance to upgrade to a private car)</li>
<li>Scenic rail transfer on the ‘Bergen Railway’ from Mydral to Oslo</li>
<li>Infamous Fl<span>å</span>m Railway excursion </li>
<li>Northern Lights Xperium, in Oslo</li>
<li>Sightseeing tour of Bergen and Oslo</li>
<li>Scenic coastal ferry cruise from Bergen to Balestrand</li>
<li>Accommodation with private facilities throughout</li>
<li>6 breakfasts, 2 dinners</li>
<li><strong>Maximum Group Size: </strong>40</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Optional Tour Activities </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bergen Sightseeing Cruise with light dinner <em>(Day 2 at 17:00, approx. 1.5 hours)</em></li>
<li>Bergen Food Tour <em>(Day 2 at 15:00, approx. 3 hours)</em></li>
<li>Fjærland Full Day Tour <em>(Day 4 - pre-booking is recommended)</em></li>
</ul>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Your Hotels</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Bergen</strong> - <a data-udi="umb://document/0d46aba9adc646f2afb1eeefe50bbc3f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0d46aba9adc646f2afb1eeefe50bbc3f}" title="Augustin Hotel">Augustin Hotel</a> ★★★+ <em>(For departures 31 May; 14 Jun; 12 July; 9<sup> </sup>&amp; 23 Aug; 6 Sep)</em></li>
<li><strong>Bergen</strong> - <a data-udi="umb://document/45293e82b1a6454783e4ddb7b4de0719" href="/{localLink:umb://document/45293e82b1a6454783e4ddb7b4de0719}" title="Grand Hotel Terminus">Grand Terminus Hotel</a> ★★★★ <em>(For departures 21 Jun; 19 Jul)</em></li>
<li><strong>Balestrand</strong> - <a data-udi="umb://document/d26dcba440054402b9ccfe7166c1ad56" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d26dcba440054402b9ccfe7166c1ad56}" title="Kviknes Hotel">Kviknes Hotel </a>★★★★</li>
<li><strong>Oslo</strong> - <a data-udi="umb://document/7c5670153b2148a1afd70d7af57a24a8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7c5670153b2148a1afd70d7af57a24a8}" title="Clarion Hotel the Hub">Clarion Hotel the Hub</a> ★★★★</li>
</ul>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Departure dates</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>31 May 2020</li>
<li>14 June 2020</li>
<li>21 June 2020</li>
<li>12 July 2020</li>
<li>19 July 2020</li>
<li>09 August 2020</li>
<li>23 August 2020</li>
<li>06 September 2020</li>
</ul>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Departure flights to Bergen from:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Direct: Gatwick, Manchester &amp; Aberdeen</li>
<li>Indirect flights: via Amsterdam from regional airports available on request</li>
<li>Flight supplements may apply</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Our tours are subject to minimum numbers and with that in mind the tours and their itineraries may be subject to change. Where this becomes necessary, and where practicable, we will take the steps as outlined in clause 5 of our <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/legal/terms-conditions">terms and conditions</a>.</em></p>
